1
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:38,167
<i>You were still trying
to call someone!</i>

2
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:39,867
<i> You're my daughter!</i>

3
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,233
<i>- Hazel!
- Mommy!</i>

4
00:00:41,367 --> 00:00:43,600
<i>- You're so stubborn!
- Mom!</i>

5
00:00:43,733 --> 00:00:45,600
<i>-Hazel!
-Why are you like this, Jessica?</i>

6
00:00:45,733 --> 00:00:47,133
<i> Why do you keep doing this?</i>

7
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:48,167
<i>- Dad!
- Manuel!</i>

8
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:49,400
<i> Sorry about that.</i>

9
00:00:49,533 --> 00:00:51,433
<i>That's all my phone
could manage.</i>

10
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:55,000
<i>What matters is that we know
they're in Camalig.</i>

11
00:00:55,133 --> 00:00:56,433
<i>Give me your
and your dad's passports.</i>

12
00:00:56,567 --> 00:00:58,333
<i> We don't have them here.</i>

13
00:00:58,467 --> 00:01:00,133
<i> They left their passports.</i>

14
00:01:00,267 --> 00:01:02,633
<i>This is Jessica's.
And Manuel's.</i>

15
00:01:02,767 --> 00:01:05,767
<i>Can you give me some money
so I can buy something outside?</i>

16
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:08,300
<i>You really think I'd trust you
to leave this house?</i>

17
00:01:08,467 --> 00:01:09,567
<i> Go check on your dad first.</i>

18
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:15,000
<i> He might need something.</i>

19
00:01:16,167 --> 00:01:17,633
I haven't left Bulacan yet.

20
00:01:17,767 --> 00:01:19,333
I had to make a stop.

21
00:01:19,467 --> 00:01:20,567
So, how are you doing there?

22
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:22,000
<i>Is anyone still hanging
around you?</i>

23
00:01:22,133 --> 00:01:23,900
Not anymore, I think.

24
00:01:24,033 --> 00:01:25,367
<i> That's good to hear.</i>

25
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:26,467
You know what, Alice?

26
00:01:27,567 --> 00:01:29,367
Mr. and Mrs. Wilson

27
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:30,567
<i>already sent the money
I asked for,</i>

28
00:01:30,700 --> 00:01:33,100
and even the extra
for our plane tickets

29
00:01:33,233 --> 00:01:35,300
back to Canada,
they also send it.

30
00:01:35,433 --> 00:01:38,500
<i>- Amazing, right?
- Wow! Congratulations!</i>

31
00:01:38,633 --> 00:01:39,667
But how?

32
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:42,367
Jessica and Manuel don't have
their passports.

33
00:01:43,567 --> 00:01:44,533
Exactly.

34
00:01:44,667 --> 00:01:46,167
That's why I still have to check
with the embassy

35
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:47,167
on what to do.

36
00:01:47,300 --> 00:01:49,100
<i> - Such a hassle.
-</i> Chill.

37
00:01:49,233 --> 00:01:51,900
So Jessica's cooperating
with you now?

38
00:01:52,033 --> 00:01:53,400
<i> Oh, no way.</i>

39
00:01:53,533 --> 00:01:55,633
I caught her calling Abel.

40
00:01:55,767 --> 00:01:58,667
I really can't trust that kid.

41
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:01,000
And yet, you left them alone.

42
00:02:01,133 --> 00:02:05,000
So what if Jessica goes out and
asks the neighbors for help?

43
00:02:05,133 --> 00:02:07,567
All the doors and windows
are locked

44
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:08,800
from the outside.

45
00:02:08,933 --> 00:02:10,967
My traitor daughter can't get
out.

46
00:02:12,267 --> 00:02:13,700
Hey, wait.

47
00:02:13,867 --> 00:02:17,067
How's your nosy neighbor doing,
by the way?

48
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:19,400
Oh, you mean Miss Nita?

49
00:02:19,533 --> 00:02:20,567
She's so annoying.

50
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:23,267
I regret ever giving her
my number.

51
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,533
She keeps calling.

52
00:02:24,667 --> 00:02:27,200
Asking if I need anything.

53
00:02:27,333 --> 00:02:29,400
- Well...
- at least she's concerned.

54
00:02:29,533 --> 00:02:31,200
<i> More like a pest!</i>

55
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:32,300
Anyway,

56
00:02:32,433 --> 00:02:34,400
can't you really come with me
on this errand?

57
00:02:34,533 --> 00:02:36,700
I'm really sorry, friend.

58
00:02:36,833 --> 00:02:40,367
I already agreed
to a shift extension.

59
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:43,133
All right then,
I'm heading out.

60
00:02:43,267 --> 00:02:45,667
Okay, take care, bye.

61
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:48,467
We're not stopping
until we find Dad, okay?

62
00:02:48,633 --> 00:02:50,233
Are there still houses
around here?

63
00:02:50,367 --> 00:02:51,700
There, look! Wait, wait!
Here, here, here!

64
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:53,500
- Huh? What?
- Hold on! This is it!

65
00:03:03,967 --> 00:03:06,233
This must be Nita's Store
Jessica mentioned.

66
00:03:06,367 --> 00:03:07,367
Yes, you're right.

67
00:03:11,067 --> 00:03:12,433
Let's ask.

68
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:13,533
Good afternoon, Ma'am.

69
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:18,667
Do you happen to know
where the Capistranos live?

70
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:21,600
Are you the carpenters Hazel
hired?

71
00:03:21,767 --> 00:03:23,900
The ones fixing up their house?

72
00:03:27,367 --> 00:03:28,267
Yes, Ma'am, that's us.

73
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,967
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Ah! There.

74
00:03:30,100 --> 00:03:32,700
Oh! Over there!
See that old brown gate?

75
00:03:32,833 --> 00:03:35,567
There are plants outside,
that's the one.

76
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:37,467
Thank you, Ma'am.

77
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:38,467
We'll get going.

78
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,600
All right then,
If you need snacks,

79
00:03:40,733 --> 00:03:41,667
buy them here, okay?

80
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:42,900
Yes, Ma'am.

81
00:03:43,033 --> 00:03:53,000
Uncle, we won't stop until
we're with Dad again, okay?

82
00:04:07,367 --> 00:04:08,800
- Hazel.
<i> - Hello?</i>

83
00:04:08,933 --> 00:04:11,900
So today's the start
of your house repairs?

84
00:04:12,033 --> 00:04:13,800
<i>- What?
- Ah, oh...</i>

85
00:04:13,933 --> 00:04:16,367
If you need an extra helper,

86
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:18,567
my grandson Virgilio
is available.

87
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:20,567
<i> What? Huh?</i>

88
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:22,100
<i>What are you talking about,
Miss Nita?</i>

89
00:04:22,233 --> 00:04:25,300
Your carpenters,
they're at your house now.

90
00:04:25,433 --> 00:04:26,633
<i> What?</i>

91
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:28,133
<i> There are people in my house?</i>

92
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:30,433
Yes, they just arrived.

93
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:35,667
What happened?

94
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:45,600
Uncle, there's no car outside.

95
00:04:45,733 --> 00:04:47,400
- What?
- No car.

96
00:04:47,533 --> 00:04:49,067
That doesn't mean no one's home.

97
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,733
Maybe they just took the car.

98
00:04:53,967 --> 00:04:54,833
Jessica?

99
00:04:55,867 --> 00:04:56,733
Je...

100
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:59,633
Uncle, keep your voice down,
Hazel might hear us.

101
00:05:01,667 --> 00:05:02,700
Be quiet.

102
00:05:05,433 --> 00:05:07,067
I just need to get something.

103
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:08,167
Jessica?

104
00:05:09,533 --> 00:05:11,000
Keep it down.

105
00:05:11,133 --> 00:05:21,100
Jessica.

106
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:37,000
Open it now! Hurry, hurry!

107
00:05:40,967 --> 00:05:45,667
Jessica?

108
00:05:46,967 --> 00:05:48,800
Jessica?

109
00:05:48,933 --> 00:05:49,900
Jessica?

110
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:59,767
- Jessica?
- Jessica?

111
00:06:00,967 --> 00:06:02,200
Jessica!

112
00:06:04,767 --> 00:06:06,233
- Jessica!
- Jessica!

113
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:10,033
Jeffrey.

114
00:06:10,167 --> 00:06:11,600
- Jessica?
- Jeffrey!

115
00:06:12,667 --> 00:06:14,600
- Jeffrey!
- Oh! Jessica! Jessica!

116
00:06:14,733 --> 00:06:16,833
- Are you okay?
- Uncle!

117
00:06:16,967 --> 00:06:18,500
Jeffrey, mom's not here.

118
00:06:19,567 --> 00:06:28,633
Get dad ready, okay?

119
00:06:32,933 --> 00:06:34,900
All right, I got this.

120
00:06:35,033 --> 00:06:36,267
Dad.

121
00:06:38,067 --> 00:06:39,100
Dad.

122
00:06:39,233 --> 00:06:41,000
Dad, you need to wake up.

123
00:06:41,667 --> 00:06:45,167
Jeffrey and Uncle Abel are here,
Dad.

124
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:46,833
They're coming up.

125
00:06:48,733 --> 00:06:50,733
You're going home now, Dad,
home to your family.

126
00:06:51,933 --> 00:06:53,633
To our family.

127
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:00,000
Bro?

128
00:07:18,367 --> 00:07:19,367
Dad.

129
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:25,433
Dad, I'm here.

130
00:07:25,567 --> 00:07:26,700
It's me, Jeff.

131
00:07:30,367 --> 00:07:31,767
Son.

132
00:07:35,233 --> 00:07:36,300
Sorry.

133
00:07:40,933 --> 00:07:42,233
I'm sorry, Dad.

134
00:07:43,467 --> 00:07:44,400
Sorry.

135
00:07:44,533 --> 00:07:46,267
I'm sorry.

136
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:48,433
I'm sorry, Dad.

137
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:50,133
I didn't get there right away.

138
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:52,467
Sorry, sorry.

139
00:07:52,600 --> 00:08:02,400
I'm sorry, Dad.

140
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:04,733
I'm here now, Dad.

141
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:08,833
I'm here,
I'm here.

142
00:08:10,367 --> 00:08:11,733
Your son is here.

143
00:08:19,967 --> 00:08:22,733
Can't we just call them instead?

144
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,667
Coleen, we agreed

145
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:28,033
they'll be the ones to call us,
so they won't lose focus, okay?

146
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,133
Coleen, stop insisting.

147
00:08:36,133 --> 00:08:37,333
It's Joel.

148
00:08:37,467 --> 00:08:39,000
It's Joel, honey.

149
00:08:41,367 --> 00:08:42,467
Hello, Joel?

150
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:48,000
Oh, thank God!

151
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:49,700
Joel, thank you.

152
00:08:49,833 --> 00:08:51,733
Thank you so much.

153
00:08:52,367 --> 00:08:53,733
Take care.

154
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:55,567
Take care, okay?

155
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:57,267
Please take care of Manuel.

156
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,967
We're heading
to the hospital now.

157
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:02,500
We'll meet you there.

158
00:09:02,633 --> 00:09:04,233
Thank you.

159
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:19,333
Dad, are you sure
nothing hurts?

160
00:09:19,467 --> 00:09:21,100
- I'm fine, I can handle it.
- Dad, are you okay?

161
00:09:21,233 --> 00:09:22,333
Are you sure?

162
00:09:22,467 --> 00:09:24,233
- Okay, okay, here, here.
- I'll go first, I'll go first.

163
00:09:26,267 --> 00:09:27,400
There you go.

164
00:09:29,233 --> 00:09:30,133
All right.

165
00:09:49,267 --> 00:09:50,667
Jessica, come on,
let's go home.

166
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:58,833
Come on.

167
00:10:12,067 --> 00:10:12,967
Dad, we're taking you to the
hospital, okay?

168
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:14,433
You need to see a doctor.

169
00:10:15,667 --> 00:10:16,700
Son, no need.

170
00:10:17,733 --> 00:10:19,533
I feel fine.

171
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,133
Let's just go straight home.

172
00:10:21,267 --> 00:10:23,400
I'll recover there instead.

173
00:10:23,533 --> 00:10:25,400
Dad, you may feel fine

174
00:10:25,533 --> 00:10:27,667
but you still need
to see a doctor.

175
00:10:28,700 --> 00:10:30,300
Please, Dad,
listen to my sister.

176
00:10:32,133 --> 00:10:34,067
Don't be stubborn, please.

177
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:45,133
Darn it, someone blocked
the road!

178
00:10:47,567 --> 00:10:48,800
Get them out!

179
00:10:53,767 --> 00:10:55,633
Hey! Hey!

180
00:10:55,767 --> 00:10:58,167
Where are you taking Manuel?
Where are you taking him?

181
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:00,600
Aren't you scared
of the restraining order, huh?

182
00:11:00,733 --> 00:11:03,167
I'll sue you!
I'll sue all of you!

183
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:04,400
Jessica, get out of that car!

184
00:11:04,533 --> 00:11:06,167
Get out now! Jessica!

185
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:10,600
Actually, I was not
really comfortable

186
00:11:10,733 --> 00:11:12,700
having Manuel discharged.

187
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:13,867
Okay?

188
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,333
His condition is still
very delicate.

189
00:11:16,467 --> 00:11:19,067
However, the DAMA form,

190
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:21,867
the Discharge Against
Medical Advice.

191
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,567
as already signed,
Nurse Gayle witnessed it.

192
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:28,267
Yes, Doctor, I was in the ICU
when Ma'am Hazel had

193
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:32,400
Sir Manuel sign the insurance
and DAMA documents.

194
00:11:32,533 --> 00:11:36,567
Did you see Manuel himself sign
the discharge form?

195
00:11:36,700 --> 00:11:39,700
I'm sorry, I saw him signing
some papers,

196
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:41,500
but I didn't get
to check each page.

197
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:44,333
I was also monitoring
his vital signs.

198
00:11:45,500 --> 00:11:47,333
Where are the documents now?

199
00:11:47,467 --> 00:11:49,833
Actually, I called Nurse Miles.

200
00:11:49,967 --> 00:11:51,633
Okay? She's on her way.

201
00:11:51,767 --> 00:11:53,867
I actually had her photocopy
the forms.

202
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:56,067
Let me call her first, okay?

203
00:12:00,533 --> 00:12:02,100
Jessica, get out of the car!

204
00:12:02,233 --> 00:12:03,567
Bring Manuel out now!

205
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:05,833
Big brother Jeffrey,
I'll get down.

206
00:12:05,967 --> 00:12:08,667
I'll distract Mommy
so you can get Dad away.

207
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,400
- Jessi...
- I'll sue you!

208
00:12:10,533 --> 00:12:11,700
Hazel's just going to hurt you!

209
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,400
Dad, don't worry about me.

210
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:17,567
What matters is that you get
to the hospital, okay?

211
00:12:19,033 --> 00:12:20,800
Jessica, you're not getting out.

212
00:12:20,933 --> 00:12:22,300
You're coming with us,
we're not leaving you behind.

213
00:12:22,433 --> 00:12:23,667
You're coming home with us.

214
00:12:26,567 --> 00:12:27,733
Jessica! Get out of there!

215
00:12:28,333 --> 00:12:29,500
<i> Hello, Dr. Richard.</i>

216
00:12:29,633 --> 00:12:31,300
<i>I'm sorry,
I'm already on my way.</i>

217
00:12:31,433 --> 00:12:33,733
Yes, yes, Miles, It's okay,
okay, It's okay.

218
00:12:33,867 --> 00:12:36,600
Actually, we're in your office
right now.

219
00:12:36,733 --> 00:12:38,800
Where are the forms the ones
I asked you to photocopy

220
00:12:38,933 --> 00:12:39,700
for Patient Manuel.

221
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:40,900
Where is it?

222
00:12:41,033 --> 00:12:42,933
<i> They're in my tray, Doc.</i>

223
00:12:43,067 --> 00:12:44,167
The tray on the table?

224
00:12:44,967 --> 00:12:46,367
The brown folder on top?

225
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:48,100
Ah, okay.

226
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:50,933
<i>- All right, Doc.
- Okay, got it.</i>

227
00:12:51,067 --> 00:12:53,133
Okay, thank you,
thank you, bye.

228
00:12:56,433 --> 00:13:01,633
These are the documents.

229
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:07,133
Oh...

230
00:13:07,733 --> 00:13:08,867
The signatures look similar.

231
00:13:11,933 --> 00:13:12,967
See here?

232
00:13:14,933 --> 00:13:17,267
On the insurance form...

233
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:21,700
the end of the signature
curves upward.

234
00:13:21,867 --> 00:13:24,967
It's consistent on every page.

235
00:13:27,367 --> 00:13:29,367
Bring Manuel
out of that car! Hey!

236
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:30,467
Jessica.

237
00:13:31,667 --> 00:13:33,300
Jessica, hold Dad tight, okay?

238
00:13:33,433 --> 00:13:34,467
Dad, hang on!

239
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:39,500
Let's go!

240
00:13:41,867 --> 00:13:43,300
Get out of that car!

241
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,233
Hey! Manuel!

242
00:13:54,933 --> 00:13:56,300
Dad, are you okay?

243
00:13:58,167 --> 00:14:00,367
You idiots!
You're all so stupid!

244
00:14:02,900 --> 00:14:04,367
But on the discharge form...

245
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:06,867
the signature tails downward.

246
00:14:07,667 --> 00:14:09,467
So you're saying
this is a forgery?

247
00:14:11,567 --> 00:14:14,300
But you know what? We don't have
to argue about this now.

248
00:14:14,433 --> 00:14:15,733
Manuel is on his way.

249
00:14:17,133 --> 00:14:18,400
My eldest is bringing him here.

250
00:14:18,533 --> 00:14:21,867
Let's just ask him if he
actually signed these papers.

251
00:14:23,333 --> 00:14:29,233
If we can prove Manuel didn't
sign these documents...

252
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:31,267
he can press charges.

253
00:14:32,267 --> 00:14:34,800
Forgery against Hazel.

254
00:14:34,933 --> 00:14:37,133
and an administrative complaint
against you.

255
00:14:37,267 --> 00:14:41,800
For negligence and violation
of hospital protocol.

256
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:45,833
But I don't want to fight you
over this.

257
00:14:45,967 --> 00:14:49,167
What I want is for Manuel
to recover.

258
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:52,300
Take care of him, heal him.

259
00:14:52,433 --> 00:14:54,833
Then we won't have
any more problems.

260
00:14:54,967 --> 00:14:58,133
I'll tell Manuel
not to file charges.

261
00:14:58,367 --> 00:14:59,833
We will get it done.

262
00:14:59,967 --> 00:15:01,833
- May I?
- Thank you, Doctor.

263
00:15:07,300 --> 00:15:08,467
Miss Felma, wait.

264
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:10,800
If I may, one more time.

265
00:15:11,733 --> 00:15:13,200
May I apologize? Okay?

266
00:15:13,333 --> 00:15:15,733
The hospital is not
at fault here.

267
00:15:15,867 --> 00:15:17,533
This is totally on me.

268
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:18,800
Okay?

269
00:15:18,933 --> 00:15:21,767
I should have checked the papers
before Manuel signed.

270
00:15:21,900 --> 00:15:24,567
I should have talked with Manuel
before he signed.

271
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:26,500
I was not able to do that.

272
00:15:26,633 --> 00:15:29,900
Okay, but let me promise you,
I assure you,

273
00:15:30,033 --> 00:15:32,200
we will get this done.
We will have this fixed.

274
00:15:32,633 --> 00:15:35,233
- Okay?
- Thank you, Doctor.

275
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:39,467
Harris, move faster!

276
00:15:40,267 --> 00:15:41,467
You're useless!

277
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,200
We couldn't catch up!

278
00:15:47,300 --> 00:15:48,267
Hello?

279
00:15:49,367 --> 00:15:52,100
Abel took Manuel, Alice.

280
00:15:52,233 --> 00:15:53,500
He ran away with him.

281
00:15:53,633 --> 00:15:54,767
That's why I called.

282
00:15:54,900 --> 00:15:56,233
Felma is here.

283
00:15:56,367 --> 00:15:58,067
She just spoke with Dr. Richard.

284
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,100
<i> What?</i>

285
00:15:59,233 --> 00:16:01,067
You mean they're bringing
Manuel there?

286
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:03,100
<i>That Felma is really testing me.</i>

287
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:05,233
She wants war?
Fine, I'll give her war.

288
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:06,900
I have to go now.

289
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:11,800
Harris, hurry!

290
00:16:11,933 --> 00:16:13,300
You're so slow!

291
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:18,000
Did Hazel really forge
Manuel's signature?

292
00:16:19,900 --> 00:16:21,433
Come on!

293
00:16:21,567 --> 00:16:23,933
Why do you keep tolerating
your friend?

294
00:16:25,967 --> 00:16:29,600
Our friend, Miles.

295
00:16:29,733 --> 00:16:31,033
You know what's going on, right?

296
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,367
Felma's been pestering Hazel.

297
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:36,400
She just wants to keep Manuel
away from her.

298
00:16:36,533 --> 00:16:37,567
That's all.

299
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:40,167
At the expense
of her husband's health?

300
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:41,900
Miles...

301
00:16:43,233 --> 00:16:44,700
Hazel is a good nurse.

302
00:16:45,667 --> 00:16:49,000
She knows how to take care
of her husband.

303
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:50,733
Let's just try
to understand her.

304
00:16:50,867 --> 00:16:52,100
She's been through a lot.

305
00:16:53,267 --> 00:16:55,600
Oh, really, Alice?

306
00:16:55,733 --> 00:16:57,833
Is she the only one who's going
through something?

307
00:16:58,933 --> 00:17:00,900
But you know what, this time,

308
00:17:01,033 --> 00:17:03,267
she has really crossed the line.

309
00:17:04,833 --> 00:17:08,933
But why am I even surprised?

310
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:11,200
We're talking about Hazel here.

311
00:17:11,333 --> 00:17:13,767
She's been like that since
college.

312
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:18,033
She doesn't care who she uses,

313
00:17:18,167 --> 00:17:22,133
who she steps on,
or who gets dragged down,

314
00:17:22,267 --> 00:17:24,200
as long as she gets
what she wants.

315
00:17:28,833 --> 00:17:30,467
Is Mr. Manuel Cruz here yet?

316
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,367
He should be arriving
any minute now.

317
00:17:34,300 --> 00:17:35,833
Trauma Bay 1!

318
00:17:36,767 --> 00:17:37,900
Dad.

319
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:45,200
Mr. Manuel, welcome back.

320
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:46,533
How are you feeling?

321
00:17:46,667 --> 00:17:47,900
I'm okay, Doc.

322
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:50,033
Only the patient can enter
the trauma bay.

323
00:17:50,167 --> 00:17:53,967
Doctor, please, can Jessica
come in just for a moment?

324
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:55,933
I just need to say something.

325
00:17:56,067 --> 00:17:57,867
All right, no problem.

326
00:18:03,667 --> 00:18:04,800
Where's Mom?

327
00:18:05,633 --> 00:18:07,933
There's an emergency at FMP,

328
00:18:08,067 --> 00:18:10,233
but she's coming here soon.

329
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:15,467
Doc, I took his vitals earlier.

330
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:18,533
BP is 60 over 60,
heart rate 112,

331
00:18:18,667 --> 00:18:21,367
but his oxygen stat
is dropping to 89 percent.

332
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:24,767
Okay, switch his nasal cannula
to a face mask,

333
00:18:24,933 --> 00:18:25,900
5 liters per minute.

334
00:18:26,033 --> 00:18:27,833
How's the chest tube?

335
00:18:27,967 --> 00:18:28,900
Nothing, Doc.

336
00:18:29,033 --> 00:18:31,067
Chest tube intact, no leaks.

337
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,533
No leak? No bubbles?

338
00:18:32,667 --> 00:18:33,667
None, Doc.

339
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:35,600
Okay, good.

340
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,600
How are you feeling, Manuel?

341
00:18:37,733 --> 00:18:39,700
Ah, I'm okay, Doc.

342
00:18:40,367 --> 00:18:44,300
I actually feel better
after seeing my kids.

343
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:46,567
Good, glad to hear.

344
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:48,500
All right, let's do this.

345
00:18:48,633 --> 00:18:55,067
CBC, X-ray, stat,
set up his previous antibiotics,

346
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:58,167
And we'll finish your admission.

347
00:18:58,300 --> 00:19:00,733
Okay? Okay, come on, let's go.

348
00:19:03,900 --> 00:19:05,467
Thank you so much.

349
00:19:06,567 --> 00:19:08,600
You never left me
from the very start.

350
00:19:10,033 --> 00:19:11,967
How are you feeling now?

351
00:19:12,467 --> 00:19:14,767
I feel fine, Dad.

352
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:15,933
I'm relieved.

353
00:19:16,900 --> 00:19:19,767
I'm so happy you're finally
here and safe.

354
00:19:21,467 --> 00:19:23,967
Dear, you know your mom won't
stop

355
00:19:24,100 --> 00:19:25,733
until she finds us...

356
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,133
right?

357
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:33,033
If she comes here,
don't go near her.

358
00:19:33,300 --> 00:19:34,733
Stay away.

359
00:19:34,867 --> 00:19:37,000
Better yet, go to your siblings.

360
00:19:37,133 --> 00:19:39,433
I know they'll protect you,

361
00:19:39,567 --> 00:19:42,000
especially your older
brother Jeffrey.

362
00:19:42,133 --> 00:19:43,167
Okay, Dad.

363
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:49,067
Love you, Dad.

364
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:54,600
I love you too, sweetheart,
so... so much.

365
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,933
I'll step out for a bit, Dad.

366
00:19:58,433 --> 00:19:59,900
We'll be right outside, okay?

367
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:09,833
All right.

368
00:20:10,567 --> 00:20:11,733
Love you, Dad.

369
00:20:12,967 --> 00:20:14,600
I love you. I love you.

370
00:20:14,733 --> 00:20:16,667
I love you, Dad.

371
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:18,200
I love you so much.

372
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:21,067
What's this?

373
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:22,733
That's a lot of "I love you's."

374
00:20:22,867 --> 00:20:24,033
You took all of it.

375
00:20:24,967 --> 00:20:26,033
Sweetheart...

376
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:28,367
just remember...

377
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:33,433
I love you very, very much.

378
00:20:33,567 --> 00:20:35,000
Never forget that.

379
00:20:35,167 --> 00:20:36,933
I'll never forget, Dad.

380
00:20:41,067 --> 00:20:41,833
So here's what happened,
Darling.

381
00:20:41,967 --> 00:20:42,933
I drove the van straight
ahead, right?

382
00:20:43,067 --> 00:20:44,433
Then suddenly, this white van
blocked the road.

383
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:47,900
Two guys went out, both carrying
baseball bats.

384
00:20:48,033 --> 00:20:49,033
They were about to smash us!

385
00:20:49,167 --> 00:20:50,533
They thought I'd be scared.

386
00:20:50,667 --> 00:20:53,400
But I hit the gas,
just like that, drove off fast.

387
00:20:53,533 --> 00:20:54,433
The two of them went down!

388
00:20:54,567 --> 00:20:55,733
I thought they were done for.

389
00:20:55,867 --> 00:20:58,500
But they got back up.
Then Hazel showed up,

390
00:20:58,633 --> 00:21:01,067
furious, banging on the van.

391
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:03,333
She thought I'd back away.

392
00:21:03,467 --> 00:21:05,200
But Jeff and I just looked
at each other.

393
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:08,567
And with that look alone,
we both knew.

394
00:21:08,733 --> 00:21:09,867
So I stepped on the gas, hard!

395
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:13,433
Sped off, all the way down
the other street.

396
00:21:13,567 --> 00:21:17,033
Hazel tried to chase us,
but she couldn't catch up.

397
00:21:17,167 --> 00:21:18,200
They were gone.

398
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:19,667
When I looked back,
they were gone.

399
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:22,167
Darling, she really thought
she could stop us.

400
00:21:22,733 --> 00:21:24,900
Wow! You were amazing, darling.

401
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:25,933
Like a real hero!

402
00:21:26,067 --> 00:21:27,900
But wait, I have a question.

403
00:21:28,033 --> 00:21:31,100
You said you backed up
when you saw Hazel, right?

404
00:21:31,233 --> 00:21:34,567
Why didn't you just go forward
and run her over?

405
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:35,700
Actually, Auntie Paz,

406
00:21:35,833 --> 00:21:37,900
that's what I thought Uncle Abel
was going to do.

407
00:21:38,300 --> 00:21:39,267
Just graze her a little.

408
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:42,900
Graze? You should've hit her!

409
00:21:43,067 --> 00:21:44,233
Darling, of course not.

410
00:21:44,367 --> 00:21:45,500
I couldn't do that.

411
00:21:45,633 --> 00:21:46,600
That's bad.

412
00:21:46,733 --> 00:21:49,467
- That was a bit too much.
- Sorry, sorry.

413
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:50,500
I just got...

414
00:21:50,633 --> 00:21:52,967
too worked up over that witch.

415
00:21:53,100 --> 00:21:54,933
Didn't mean what I said.

416
00:21:55,067 --> 00:21:56,667
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

417
00:22:06,967 --> 00:22:08,767
We need to talk.

418
00:22:12,233 --> 00:22:13,600
Vitals normal, Nurse?

419
00:22:14,367 --> 00:22:18,233
All right,
Okay, okay.

420
00:22:19,167 --> 00:22:20,100
Then...

421
00:22:20,233 --> 00:22:22,800
No leaks there? Good.

422
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:26,767
All right, let's remove
your chest tube now, Manuel.

423
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,200
Oh.

424
00:22:30,567 --> 00:22:31,867
Oh. Okay, I'll give you
some time.

425
00:22:34,267 --> 00:22:36,900
- Felma....
- Manuel.

426
00:23:00,933 --> 00:23:01,300
Coleen, what's your problem?

427
00:23:01,433 --> 00:23:02,633
Let go of me!

428
00:23:03,467 --> 00:23:05,067
- Coleen! Hey!
- Come here!

429
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,833
Coleen!

430
00:23:06,967 --> 00:23:08,600
What's wrong with you?

431
00:23:09,633 --> 00:23:12,467
How could you just let your mom
take Dad away?

432
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:14,200
We were all worried sick!

433
00:23:14,333 --> 00:23:16,467
I tried to stop her!

434
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:17,933
Really?

435
00:23:18,067 --> 00:23:20,000
You didn't even ask Andrea
for help

436
00:23:20,133 --> 00:23:21,767
when you and your mom were
sneaking Dad out!

437
00:23:22,300 --> 00:23:24,167
You even avoided her,
didn't you?

438
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:26,833
And when Jeffrey and I were
trying to reach you,

439
00:23:26,967 --> 00:23:28,733
what did you do?

440
00:23:28,867 --> 00:23:30,433
You insulted us!

441
00:23:31,467 --> 00:23:33,600
You just liked my messages.

442
00:23:33,733 --> 00:23:35,600
And when Jeffrey called,
you answered,

443
00:23:35,733 --> 00:23:38,200
but didn't even say a word!

444
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:39,933
Coleen, that wasn't me.

445
00:23:40,067 --> 00:23:41,600
Mom confiscated my phone.

446
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:44,333
Jessica, stop lying!

447
00:23:45,633 --> 00:23:47,733
Of course, you're on Mom's side,

448
00:23:47,867 --> 00:23:49,600
because you want Dad away
from us too!

449
00:23:49,733 --> 00:23:51,300
That's not true!

450
00:23:51,433 --> 00:23:54,500
I stole Mom's phone so I could
call Uncle Abel, remember?

451
00:23:54,633 --> 00:23:56,367
For all I know,
you only did that

452
00:23:56,533 --> 00:23:58,367
because Dad's condition was
getting worse!

453
00:23:58,500 --> 00:24:00,433
Yes! Because I was scared

454
00:24:00,567 --> 00:24:02,267
something bad might happen
to him!

455
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:04,033
And Mom might hurt him!

456
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:08,700
But more than that, Dad wanted
to see Auntie Felma,

457
00:24:08,833 --> 00:24:11,700
Brother Jeffrey, Sister Andrea,
and you, Coleen!

458
00:24:12,733 --> 00:24:14,967
That's why I took the risk
and stole

459
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:17,967
Mom's phone to make that call!

460
00:24:18,100 --> 00:24:21,333
So what, huh?
You expect us to thank you

461
00:24:21,467 --> 00:24:23,967
because you called when Dad's
life was already in danger?

462
00:24:24,100 --> 00:24:26,733
You're so selfish, Jessica!

463
00:24:26,867 --> 00:24:29,300
You were so focused
on getting Dad away,

464
00:24:29,467 --> 00:24:31,600
you didn't even think
about his condition!

465
00:24:31,733 --> 00:24:34,600
- Coleen!
- Jessica, you didn't even think

466
00:24:34,733 --> 00:24:37,067
that something bad
could happen to him!

467
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:39,833
Jessica, is that
what a daughter does?

468
00:24:39,967 --> 00:24:41,900
You don't act like Dad's
daughter at all!

469
00:24:50,433 --> 00:24:53,600
- Andeng.
- Dad.

470
00:24:53,733 --> 00:24:55,933
You're just too jealous, Coleen!

471
00:24:56,067 --> 00:24:57,400
And you're insecure!

472
00:24:57,533 --> 00:24:59,400
I am not insecure about you!

473
00:24:59,533 --> 00:25:02,600
I wish you'd just disappear!

474
00:25:02,767 --> 00:25:04,800
- Was that Jessica?
- That sounded like Coleen.

475
00:25:04,933 --> 00:25:07,067
- Jessica!
- You want me gone, right?

476
00:25:07,200 --> 00:25:08,367
Fine, I'll leave!

477
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:09,667
I'm done with all of you!

478
00:25:12,067 --> 00:25:14,067
Jessica!

479
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:15,633
Is there something
you're not telling me?

480
00:25:16,900 --> 00:25:17,967
Is there a problem?

481
00:25:18,100 --> 00:25:19,500
You monster!

482
00:25:19,633 --> 00:25:21,167
What are you doing here?

483
00:25:21,300 --> 00:25:22,633
You don't know?
